Russian Spring Sowing Reaches 517,000 Hectares, Ministry Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-06T13:18:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/russian-spring-sowing-reaches-517-000-hectares-ministry-says.html
The Russian spring sowing area is
about 517,000 hectares (1.3 million acres) in the Southern,
North-Caucasus and Far Eastern federal districts as of today,
the  Agriculture Ministry  said in an e-mailed press release.  Of those, 294,000 hectares have been sown in Krasnodar
region, 157,000 hectares in Stavropol region, and 2,200 hectares
in Primorsk region, it said.  Sugar beets have been sown on an area of more than 94,000
hectares, most of which is in Krasnodar region.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  